On March 15th, the Jura canton in Switzerland announced conditions for the operation of essential businesses, which come into effect March 16th:

Essential and food businesses that also sell non-essential items may remain open granted that they solely sell essential items to customers;

Essential and food businesses may open from 6 am to 8 pm (except for individual establishments that were granted exceptions);

Both customers and business owners and their employees must adhere by the sanitary precautions dictated by the Federal Office of Public Health, especially in terms of social distancing (through markings on the floor for instance);

People responsible for businesses and establishments that remain open must clearly display, the sanitary measures for individual and collective protection recommended by the Federal Office of Public Health.

Switzerland, Geneva--The canton of Geneva will require the closing of public establishments, with the exception of those providing essential services, to close beginning March 16 at 6 p.m. This measure will last until March 29, but it can be extended. This applies to
- restaurants, bars, dancing clubs with on site consumption.
 Catering service offering take-out or home delivery service can continue to operate.
-  retail stores except those offering food, hygiene, household and animal feed products, as well as pharmacies and drugstores, kiosks and petrol stations offering fuel;   
-  places of entertainment, such as cinemas, theaters, museums, neighborhood houses, youth centers, sports centers;
-  economic activities related to personal grooming even if they are carried out in the home of the provider or the client;
-  prostitution;
- Hotels must limit their activity to accommodation only. Restaurants or  spa or fitness are not allowed.
All activities that are still authorized may be carried out on the express condition that all the recommendations of the FOPH concerning hygiene and distances to be kept are strictly observed.
The cantonal police may call upon the services of the municipal police to ensure compliance with the measures ordered.

