On July 13th, the Jura canton in Switzerland announced clarifications regarding the mandate to wear masks in shops and businesses for anyone above 12. The cantonal government issued the following exemptions: 
Businesses delivering services such as banks and insurance agencies which instead should have a protection plan;
Public establishments (restaurants, bars, night clubs) which should follow the Gastrosuisse protocol though mask wearing is recommended for staff;
Mixed companies which have some activities including contact with clients should have plexiglass instead for workshops and offices but use a mask when in-contact with clients when social distancing is not possible;
Businesses where using a plexiglass is possible, mask is not mandatory unless the worker is moving around the business.
